{
  "text": "It is well known that, the main rule of clustering is to minimize the compactness of each cluster, which is usually computed by the distance between objects and either cluster's centroids or medoids. However, the centroid of each cluster with irregular structure is invalid and the medoid is hard to get by using many existing encoding schemes in evolutionary algorithm. Therefore, in here, the objective functions will be established by minimizing the distance of each pair of objects in the same cluster, and they can be written as Equation [CITATION_1] .",
